title: [Epidemiology] Factors Associated With Death in Critically Ill Patients With Coronavirus Disease 2019

[Biology] “Common Cold” Coronaviruses Could Help Produce Anti-SARS-CoV-2 Immune Cells: T cells from people without a history of coronavirus infection and those who recovered from SARS in 2003 have T cells that can react to SARS-CoV-2 peptides, say research team at Duke-NUS
